	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-12T06:40:07">Porvair plc is a specialist filtration and environmental technology company. The Company is engaged in the design and manufacture of filtration and separation equipment. The Company has two operating divisions: Metals Filtration and Microfiltration. Its Metals Filtration division designs and manufactures filters for molten metal. It provides filters for the aluminum cast house industry; the filtration of gray and ductile iron, mainly for the United States auto and light truck market, and the filtration of super alloys used in the manufacture of turbine blades. The Company's Microfiltration division provides bespoke filtration solutions to the aviation, environmental laboratory and energy/industrial markets. The Company operates Microfiltration division through Porvair Filtration Group, Seal Analytical and Porvair Sciences. The Porvair Filtration Group designs and manufactures specialist filtration solutions for contamination control in hydraulic, fuel, lubrication and air systems.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-25T10:36:01">BRIEF: For the fiscal year ended 30 November 2015, Porvair plc revenues decreased 8% to L95.8M. Net income increased 10% to L7M. Revenues reflect a decrease in demand for the Company's products and services due to unfavorable market conditions. Net income reflects Distribution Costs decrease of 2% to L1.2M (expense). Dividend per share increased from L0.03 to L0.04. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items increased from L0.14 to L0.16.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
